<seg id=1> Netherlands Establishes Commission For Advancement Of Trade Office In Wuhan </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE Wuhan, April 3 (Tang Weibin reporting): The Netherlands Commission for the Advancement of Trade officially established its representative office in Wuhan recently. </seg>
<seg id=3> This is the first office that the Dutch commission has set up in China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> According to reports, the main function of the office will be to bring timely awareness of Hubei's economic conditions to the Dutch government and industry.  It will also help Dutch companies assess trade and investment possibilities, and  work as liaison between and offer consultation to Dutch and local companies and government bodies. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The Dutch ambassador to China, at the ribbon-cutting ceremony, said that the choice of Wuhan for the office over China's other cities was due its convenient water and land transportation and its optimal geographical position. </seg>
<seg id=6> The Dutch government and industry both believe that Hubei is an area with high potential, and see cooperation possibilities with the Netherlands in transportation, infrastructure, agriculture and energy resources. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Philips, the Dutch multinational corporation, cooperated with Wuhan to establish the first foreign-invested enterprise there during the 1980s, the Wuhan Yangtze Optical Fiber and Cable Company Limited. </seg>
<seg id=8> The cooperation between the two sides continued to deepen into the 1990s. </seg>
<seg id=9> Additionally, the Wuhan office of the Netherlands Bank was established not long ago. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> Meng Qingping, vice-premier of Hubei province, said that with the establishment in Hubei of the Netherlands Commission for the Advancement of Trade, the friendship and economic and trade relationship between the Dutch government and commercial and industrial sectors has reached a new stage. </seg>
<seg id=11> It is hoped that these sorts of cooperative relationships will continue to develop and be fruitful. </seg>
</p>
